<br>
I know who's bitch you are... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwitherweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Witherweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/15/02 5:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Caparelli should not play Gore.</span><hr size=1> &quot;Only reason why you would think there was no agreement is because FnF officers told you there was no agreement&quot;<br>
<br>
FnF officers said nothing about the agreement, which was why I had earlier said &quot;no one said anything, it just seemed obvious&quot;<br>
<br>
The agreement was made with the knowledge that two keys could get an entire raiding force into Sleeper's Tomb.  It's terms for failures were made knowing that every attempt would utilize the entire guild.<br>
<br>
Now both guilds can at most get as many people in there as they have keys.  If your clerics call in sick, well, then you're screwed.  If you're missing key members of your keyed force that night, then you're screwed.  This is significantly different than the non-no drop case where the absence of four or five people meant the dungeon was all but impossible.<br>
<br>
At the time the patch made the keys no drop there were about 6 Fire and Fury keys and about 4 or so Resolution keys (I don't know the exact numbers).  Those two combined could perhaps kill all the warders, but certainly neither guild could do it.  A rotation on mobs that are unkillable is silly.  Hence the rotation was latently voided.<br>
<br>
If we had 3 keys, and you had 20, you would laugh at us if we demanded a rotation and wouldn't let you kill warders one night because we wanted to go in there and die a couple dozen times.<br>
<br>
The real issue is a lack of communication.  You assumed the rotation was still in place.  I assumed it wasn't, I never even considered it to be questionable.  I believe that most Fire and Fury members also assumed it wasn't.  <br>
<br>
I'm sorry that you made that assumption and now feel betrayed.  Unless of course guild leaders secretly agreed with you to continue/reinstate the rotation, in which case everything I'm saying about there not being a rotation would be false.<br>
<br>
Witherweaver<br>
60 Wizard<br>
